#PENDRIVE SCRIPT RUN
🟢 Step 1: Create the PowerShell Script
🟢1.Open Notepad
🟢2.Paste this code:
Add-Type -AssemblyName PresentationFramework

# Create Fullscreen WPF Window
[xml]$xaml = @"
<Window xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        WindowStyle="None" ResizeMode="NoResize"
        WindowState="Maximized" Background="Black" Topmost="True">
    <Grid>
        <!-- Main Big Text -->
        <TextBlock Text="JAY MAHAKAL"
                   Foreground="Red"
                   FontSize="130"
                   FontWeight="Bold"
                   HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                   VerticalAlignment="Center"/>

        <!-- Sub Headline at Bottom -->
        <TextBlock Text="This Hacked"
                   Foreground="White"
                   FontSize="40"
                   FontWeight="Bold"
                   HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                   VerticalAlignment="Bottom"
                   Margin="0,0,0,40"/>
    </Grid>
</Window>
"@

# Load XAML
$reader = (New-Object System.Xml.XmlNodeReader $xaml)
$window = [Windows.Markup.XamlReader]::Load($reader)

# Show the window
$window.ShowDialog() | Out-Null
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🟢Save the file on your pendrive as:

hacked.ps1    
🟢(Choose All Files in "Save as type").

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


🟢 Step 2: Create the Batch File

🟢Open Notepad again.

🟢Paste this code:

@echo off
powershell.exe -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "%~dp0hacked.ps1"


🟢Save this file on your pendrive as:

RunHacked.bat


(Choose All Files again).

🟢 Step 3: Run It

🟢Plug in the pendrive

🟢Open the folder

🟢Double-click RunHacked.bat

🎉 A black window with BIG RED HACKED will appear in the middle of your screen     (EXIT FULL SCREEN ALT + A4) (TRY CTRL + C) 



